think that's when Muhammad was born.

01:06:36.350 --> 01:06:39.190 position:56%
But in any case, that's a parchment.

01:06:39.190 --> 01:06:42.620
The animal that that
Qur'an was written on lived

01:06:42.620 --> 01:06:44.930
at the same time as
the prophet Muhammad.

01:06:44.930 --> 01:06:46.550
We're quite sure about this.

01:06:46.550 --> 01:06:49.890
Now could somebody have
used an old parchment

01:06:49.890 --> 01:06:51.190
and written out the Qur'an on it?

01:06:51.190 --> 01:06:52.490
Maybe. We don't know.

01:06:52.490 --> 01:06:54.010
These things haven't been settled.

01:06:54.010 --> 01:06:58.360
But I would just signal that the
extreme skepticism and this sort

01:06:58.360 --> 01:07:03.150
of SOAS school that wanted to see
the Qur'an as a tradition that grew

01:07:03.150 --> 01:07:07.670
up over maybe two centuries,
that's increasingly implausible.

01:07:07.670 --> 01:07:14.910
The Qur'an we have is I think
ballpark for the period.

01:07:14.910 --> 01:07:17.180
And so I think we can
approach it this way.

01:07:17.180 --> 01:07:22.320
So I don't know if the surah
Isra is in the palimpsest.

01:07:22.320 --> 01:07:23.620
It's been published.

01:07:23.620 --> 01:07:24.920
I should take a look.

