But I guess the question is, is
war and conflict a prerequisite

01:08:40.840 --> 01:08:42.390
to get to an eventual peace?

01:08:42.390 --> 01:08:43.690
And is that allowed?

01:08:43.690 --> 01:08:44.990
Thank you.

01:08:44.990 --> 01:08:46.880
&gt;&gt; Juan Cole: Well in
apocalyptic literature of the time,

01:08:46.880 --> 01:08:52.300
it's quite frequently the case
that it is the seer foresees a war

01:08:52.300 --> 01:08:55.030
and conflict before peace can come.

01:08:55.030 --> 01:08:58.460 position:56%
And this is the shape of the Book
of Revelation or the Book of Daniel.

01:08:58.460 --> 01:09:02.160
And there are a number of
contemporary works both

01:09:02.160 --> 01:09:07.350
by Christians and Jews of the time
of Muhammad which have that shape.

01:09:07.350 --> 01:09:08.980
I don't find it in the Qur'an.

01:09:08.980 --> 01:09:10.930
I don't find this expectation

01:09:10.930 --> 01:09:15.730
of a conflict preceding
the outbreak of peace.

01:09:15.730 --> 01:09:24.510
Because even before the
conquest of Jerusalem,

01:09:24.510 --> 01:09:29.400
as the German scholar Noldek
[spelling assumed] dated the

01:09:29.400 --> 01:09:33.630
chapters at least, the Qur'an
is already laying out the schema

01:09:33.630 --> 01:09:37.290
where there's revelation,
there's a warning.

01:09:37.290 --> 01:09:40.900
There's signs of the
coming of the apocalypse

01:09:40.900 --> 01:09:44.690
and then there's the judgement
day and the resurrection.

01:09:44.690 --> 01:09:48.790
And those chapters don't really
bring up anything about war.

01:09:48.790 --> 01:09:53.210 position:56%
The signs of the resurrection or the
judgement day, the end of the world

01:09:53.210 --> 01:09:57.710
in the Qur'an tend to be natural.

01:09:57.710 --> 01:10:03.630
So that will be a day on which you
know, the mountains are like wool

01:10:03.630 --> 01:10:09.070
that you carted from a sheep and
will just be blown by the wind.

01:10:09.070 --> 01:10:12.320
And the stars will fall
and lose their brightness.

01:10:12.320 --> 01:10:14.860
So the signs in the Qur'an

01:10:14.860 --> 01:10:19.610
for the judgement day aren't
typically the marching of armies.

01:10:19.610 --> 01:10:24.600
And one of the early verses which
does have a social content says

01:10:24.600 --> 01:10:27.690
that will be the day on
which the unborn child,

01:10:27.690 --> 01:10:32.410
the unborn girls will
ask why was she killed?

01:10:32.410 --> 01:10:36.390
And you know, in premodern
societies --

01:10:36.390 --> 01:10:39.110 position:56%
or the newborn girls I meant to say.

01:10:39.110 --> 01:10:40.410
In premodern societies,

01:10:40.410 --> 01:10:44.530
female infanticide was
a birth control method.

01:10:44.530 --> 01:10:51.900
And archaeologists in Egypt have
found large numbers of you know,

01:10:51.900 --> 01:10:56.070
babies basically who
were killed in this way.

01:10:56.070 --> 01:10:59.610
An anthropologist will
tell you that the fertility

01:10:59.610 --> 01:11:03.940
of a group is determined by
the number of women in it.

01:11:03.940 --> 01:11:09.910
And so if a famine has come,
if it's hard days and so forth,

01:11:09.910 --> 01:11:13.630
people at that time would
often kill their girl children,

01:11:13.630 --> 01:11:14.930
their girl babies.

01:11:14.930 --> 01:11:18.210
And the Qur'an remonstrates
with them.

01:11:18.210 --> 01:11:20.430
It think that this is very evil.

01:11:20.430 --> 01:11:24.270
So the feminist corner of the
Qur'an that's defending the girls.

01:11:24.270 --> 01:11:29.850 position:56%
But it says that on the resurrection
day, you know, the babies will ask,

01:11:29.850 --> 01:11:32.020
"What did we do to deserve this?"

01:11:32.020 --> 01:11:37.300
So that's the major social
intervention that I can think

01:11:37.300 --> 01:11:39.430
of with regard to the
apocalypse in the Qur'an.

01:11:39.430 --> 01:11:47.400 position:56%
So no, with regard to ISIL, a lot of
those guys were ex-Bothe military.

01:11:47.400 --> 01:11:50.460
I don't know if you've ever hung
around with ex-Bothe military,

01:11:50.460 --> 01:11:53.500
but I don't think they
know how to pray.

01:11:53.500 --> 01:11:59.510
And they like a good stiff
glass of whiskey, am I right?

01:11:59.510 --> 01:12:02.100
[ Inaudible ]

01:12:02.100 --> 01:12:05.520
Yeah, Abu Bakr, the leader
of ISIL does have a PhD,

01:12:05.520 --> 01:12:07.280
but a lot of those guys with him,

01:12:07.280 --> 01:12:10.370
they're just dusted
off Bothe officers.

01:12:10.370 --> 01:12:14.910
So I think they're manipulating
you know Islam for their purposes.

01:12:14.910 --> 01:12:18.960
Yeah, I don't think
it's sincere with them.

01:12:18.960 --> 01:12:22.610
And some of the rank and
file might be sincere,

01:12:22.610 --> 01:12:24.640
but you know we've had a chance now

01:12:24.640 --> 01:12:26.530
to study ISIL a little
bit academically.

01:12:26.530 --> 01:12:31.250
There have been exit interviews,
because you know, people have left.

01:12:31.250 --> 01:12:34.800
Leaving is chancy because
if they figure

01:12:34.800 --> 01:12:36.610
out you're leaving
they will kill you.

01:12:36.610 --> 01:12:38.610
But some people manage to get out.

01:12:38.610 --> 01:12:42.180
And then anthropologists and
researchers have gone and talked

01:12:42.180 --> 01:12:44.940
to them about what was
it like and so forth.

01:12:44.940 --> 01:12:46.750
And they find these
people who have escaped,

01:12:46.750 --> 01:12:50.710
they often didn't know very much
about Islam in a formal sense.

01:12:50.710 --> 01:12:54.330
So the idea that Graham Wood put
forward in this Atlantic article

01:12:54.330 --> 01:12:58.610 position:56%
that you know, ISIL is very Islamic,
I don't know what he meant by that.

01:12:58.610 --> 01:13:01.020
And in fact, that seems
to me very essentialist.

01:13:01.020 --> 01:13:03.800
Like what would it mean
to be very Islamic?

01:13:03.800 --> 01:13:05.810
Are some things more
Islamic than others

01:13:05.810 --> 01:13:07.880
in some kind of essential sense?

01:13:07.880 --> 01:13:10.680
Certainly they think
they're Muslims,

01:13:10.680 --> 01:13:13.440
but you know those snake handlers

01:13:13.440 --> 01:13:17.100
in the south think that
they're Christians.

01:13:17.100 --> 01:13:19.830
Most of us, I wouldn't
want to argue with them

01:13:19.830 --> 01:13:22.560
that they're not Christians,
but we don't typically think

01:13:22.560 --> 01:13:27.680
that snake handling is in
fact central to Christianity,

01:13:27.680 --> 01:13:30.510
even though this group
maintains that that's so.

01:13:30.510 --> 01:13:34.100
So I think that the ISIL
people are more the equivalent

01:13:34.100 --> 01:13:36.220
