01:14:38.120 --> 01:14:42.340 position:56%
I'd like to get back to the Mirage,
the vision of the trip to Jerusalem.

01:14:42.340 --> 01:14:46.630
And basically in Qur'an
Jerusalem is not mentioned at all.

01:14:46.630 --> 01:14:52.310
The trip was to El Mastrida
Alexa, the furthest mosque.

01:14:52.310 --> 01:14:57.700
And the Alexa mosque in Jerusalem
wasn't even built until after 700.

01:14:57.700 --> 01:15:02.370
So how and when did that
get connected to Jerusalem?

01:15:02.370 --> 01:15:04.180
&gt;&gt; Juan Cole: Well,
that's a good question,

01:15:04.180 --> 01:15:07.980
as of course the Qur'an is often
illusive and we are interpreting it

01:15:07.980 --> 01:15:10.760
to say what we think it means.

01:15:10.760 --> 01:15:12.990
But here's my argument for it.

01:15:12.990 --> 01:15:14.490
You remember that verse I mentioned

01:15:14.490 --> 01:15:21.470
about Byzantium being defeated
in the nearest province?

01:15:21.470 --> 01:15:26.470
It says El Ardna Altna,
the nearest province.

01:15:26.470 --> 01:15:31.620
Then when it's talking about El
Mastrida Alexa, it's the farthest.

01:15:31.620 --> 01:15:33.820
Nearest, farthest.

01:15:33.820 --> 01:15:42.620
Now let me just show you the map.

01:15:44.690 --> 01:15:51.040
If you look at this map,
Mecca is in the Hijaz.

01:15:51.040 --> 01:15:57.910
If you go north into Byzantine
Syria, that's the nearest province.

01:15:57.910 --> 01:16:02.510 position:56%
And they used to go up to Gaza which
was the port on the Mediterranean.

01:16:02.510 --> 01:16:03.810
If you keep going up to Gaza,

01:16:03.810 --> 01:16:06.170
that would be the farthest
province you could get

01:16:06.170 --> 01:16:08.320
to before you got to the sea.

01:16:08.320 --> 01:16:15.210
So I think the mastrid, which is
the farthest, is in Jerusalem.

01:16:15.210 --> 01:16:20.230
And the word mastrid,
it doesn't mean mosque.

01:16:20.230 --> 01:16:24.430
We're talking 614 here,
or something.

01:16:24.430 --> 01:16:26.170
There were no mosques.

01:16:26.170 --> 01:16:32.730
And it is a Semitic word which
means something like altar.

01:16:32.730 --> 01:16:39.060
The pagans and those blocks that
I showed you would sacrifice

01:16:39.060 --> 01:16:40.360
at the bottom of the block.

01:16:40.360 --> 01:16:43.930
There would be a mastrid
or an altar.

01:16:43.930 --> 01:16:47.870
My guess is that what's
being referred

01:16:47.870 --> 01:16:57.290
to is the Basilica I Essene,
the Church of Holy Zion.

01:16:57.290 --> 01:17:01.080
Which was the only religious
structure anywhere near the temple

01:17:01.080 --> 01:17:03.990
mount at the time Muhammad
was talking.

01:17:03.990 --> 01:17:07.750
Because of course the temple itself
had been destroyed by the Romans

01:17:07.750 --> 01:17:09.900
and then there were
some synagogues up there

01:17:09.900 --> 01:17:12.140
which were destroyed
by the Christians.

01:17:12.140 --> 01:17:17.860
And so the only religious edifice
anywhere near the temple mount

01:17:17.860 --> 01:17:23.610 position:56%
on the western hill was the Basilica
of Holy Zion which was a place

01:17:23.610 --> 01:17:25.720
of pilgrimage and was
associated with some

01:17:25.720 --> 01:17:28.120
of the events of Jesus's life.

01:17:28.120 --> 01:17:31.530
And I think -- a little
bit speculative on my part,

01:17:31.530 --> 01:17:37.870
but I'm going to put it forward --
that the Qur'an sees a connection

01:17:37.870 --> 01:17:43.260
between the Kaaba in Mecca
and the Basilica in Jerusalem.

01:17:43.260 --> 01:17:47.360
And that this is an
axis and that's why

01:17:47.360 --> 01:17:50.970
for a while they prayed
towards Jerusalem.

01:17:50.970 --> 01:17:56.520
And then they switched to
praying towards the Kaaba.

01:17:56.520 --> 01:18:02.770
But both of them are worthy
of being the point of prayer

01:18:02.770 --> 01:18:05.650
and have a spiritual
connection between them.

01:18:05.650 --> 01:18:13.550
And I think the Qur'an refers
to Jerusalem as the Holy Land,

01:18:13.550 --> 01:18:17.150
and it also obviously feels
that Mecca is the Holy Land.

01:18:17.150 --> 01:18:20.820
So I think there's a kind of
sacred geography at work here.

01:18:20.820 --> 01:18:24.000
And that's how I would see it.

